Bayern Munich beat Porto 3-1 in the Champions League first leg at the Estadio do Dragao . 
  Ricardo Quaresma opened the scoring for Porto from the penalty spot in the third minute . 
  Bayern goalkeeper Manuel Neuer conceded the penalty after Jackson Martinez was fouled in the box . 
  Thiago doubled Porto's lead in the 28th minute with a close-range strike . 
  Mario Martinez made it 2-0 for the hosts in the 64th minute . 
 